Following a news report by international news outlet, the Al Jazeera news network on the lack of sensitization in Nigeria regarding the Covid-19 pandemic that has led to a global shutdown, the Northern Solidarity Front (NSF) through its Leader, Garuda Ahmed has tackled the National Orientation Agency (NOA) for not doing enough in sensitising Nigerians on the dangers associated with the virus. In a press statement released to journalists in Abuja on Friday, the group chided the NOA for sitting idle instead of carrying out its main objective that it was established to do in this time of national crisis. “It is sad that at this critical time, the NOA is doing nothing to sensitize Nigerians on the dangers associated with the covid-19 virus. If the agency had been doing it’s job, the report by Aljazeera where Nigerians were seen going about their normal lives and claiming that the virus is not in Nigeria would have been the opposite “. The statement further called for a probe of the budget of the NOA saying,” you cannot have a yearly budget and still do nothing”.
It called on the APC led government to take a cue from former Vice President Atiku Abubakar, Aliko Dangote and Tony Elumelu by providing relief stimuli for vulnerable Nigerians this period. He commended the former VP for coming to the aid of Nigerians during this critical period. It wondered the APC led government was being cautious with the situation.
“I wonder why at this critical time, instead of looking for a solution, the APC is busy playing politics by spreading falsehood about the son of the former VP who tested positive to the virus but they are mute on the case within the presidential villa.”